26920252085/an-interview-with-t-m-scanlon An Interview with T.&nbsp;M. Scanlon] by Yascha Mounk, 2012-07-07.\n* Interview with Fifteen Minutes Magazine, The Harvard Crimson. [https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2019/10/10/scanlon-and-the-good-place/ ''Asking Philosopher T. M. Scanlon \u2018What We Owe to Each Other\u2019'']\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.fas.harvard.edu/~phildept/index.html The Department of Philosophy at Harvard]\n* [https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/contractualism/ Contractualism at Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, Ashford E, Mulgan T]\n\n{{Social and political philosophy}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Scanlon, T. M.}}\n[[Category:1940 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American philosophers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American philosophers]]\n[[Category:Analytic philosophers]]\n[[Category:American philosophy academics]]\n[[Category:American political philosophers]]\n[[Category:Moral philosophers]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Princeton University alumni]]\n[[Category:Princeton University faculty]]\n[[Category:Harvard University faculty]]\n[[Category:Proof theorists]]\n[[Category:Guggenheim Fellows]]\n[[Category:Philosophers from Indiana]]\n[[Category:Writers from Indianapolis]]\n[[Category:Members of the American Philosophical Society]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the American Philosophical Association]]\n[[Category:MacArthur Fellows]]\n", "name_user": "Poldavia", "label": "safe", "comment": "+ image", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T._M._Scanlon"}
{"title_page": "Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus", "text_new": "{{Infobox religious building\n| name = Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus\n| native_name = Igreja Matriz do Sagrado Cora\u00e7\u00e3o de Jesus\n| native_name_lang = pt\n| image = Igreja Matriz de Laranjeiras.jpg\n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus\n| map_type = Brazil\n| map_size = \n| map_alt = \n| map_relief = \n| map_caption = Location of the Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus in Brazil\n| coordinates = {{coord|-10.80509|-37.16631}}\n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| religious_affiliation=[[Catholic]]\n| rite=[[Roman Rite|Roman]]\n| sect = \n| tradition = \n| festival = <!-- or | festivals = -->\n| cercle = \n| sector = \n| municipality = [[Laranjeiras, Sergipe|Laranjeiras]]\n| district = \n| territory = \n| prefecture = \n| state = [[Sergipe]]\n| province = \n| region = \n| country = [[Brazil]]\n| administration = \n| consecration_year = \n| organisational_status = <!-- or | organizational_status = -->\n| functional_status = \n| heritage_designation = 1941\n| ownership = \n| governing_body = \n| leadership = \n| bhattaraka = \n| patron = \n| website = \n| architect = \n| architecture_type = \n| architecture_style = [[Baroque architecture|Baroque]]\n| founded_by = \n| creator = \n| funded_by = \n| general_contractor = \n| established = \n| groundbreaking = \n| year_completed = 1790s\n| construction_cost = \n| date_demolished = <!-- or | date_destroyed = -->\n| facade_direction = \n| capacity = \n| length = \n| width = \n| width_nave = \n| interior_area = \n| height_max = \n| dome_quantity = \n| dome_height_outer = \n| dome_height_inner = \n| dome_dia_outer = \n| dome_dia_inner = \n| spire_quantity = \n| spire_height = \n| site_area = \n| temple_quantity = \n| monument_quantity = \n| shrine_quantity = \n| inscriptions = \n| materials = \n| elevation_m =\n| elevation_footnotes = \n| nrhp = \n| designated = \n| added = \n| refnum = \n| footnotes = {{designation list|embed = yes| designation1 = Brazil| designation1_date = 1941|designation1_number =294}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus''' ({{lang-pt|Igreja Matriz do Sagrado Cora\u00e7\u00e3o de Jesus}}) is an 18-century [[Roman Catholic]] church in [[Laranjeiras, Sergipe|Laranjeiras]], [[Sergipe]], [[Brazil]]. It was the second church built in Laranjeiras, following the [[Church of Our Lady of the Conception of Comandaroba]], which was built by the [[Jesuits]] in the early 18th century. The church was listed as a historic structure by [[National Institute of Historic and Artistic Heritage]] (IPHAN) in 1941. The church is dedicated to the [[Sacred Heart|Sacred Heart of Jesus]] and is constructed in the [[Baroque architecture|Baroque style]]. The Parish Church belongs to the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Aracaju]].<ref name=\"hpip\"/><ref name=\"iphan\"/><ref name=\"pa\"/>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Outras agendas em Sergipe (27719738197).jpg|thumb|left|250px|View of fa\u00e7ade]]\n\nConstruction of Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus began at the end of the 18th century. Residents of Laranjeiras, then a district of [[Nossa Senhora do Socorro]] with a small port on the river, petitioned [[Maria I of Portugal|Queen Maria]] for the construction of a church in 1790. With the completion of the church, Laranjeiras had two churches: the Parish Church and the [[Church of Our Lady of the Conception of Comandaroba|Church of Our Lady of the Conception]], which belonged to the Comandaroba Plantation. The church was unable to accommodate the population of Laranjeiras, which grew rapidly in the 18th century, and the building was enlarged in 1905.<ref name=\"f\"/><ref name=\"hpip\"/>\n\n==Location==\n\nThe Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus is located on a high point above a bend in the [[Cotinguiba River]]. The church faces the river but, unusually, does not open to Pra\u00e7a da Matriz. The south fa\u00e7ade of the church, which faces the public square, has numerous small portals and windows.<ref name=\"hpip\"/>\n\n==Structure==\n\nThe building has a structure consisting of mixed masonry of stone and brick. The church has two bell towers with a monumental pediment at center. The pediment has volutes and is topped by a cross. There are three windows at the choir level and a low arch with glazed leaves and flags. The bell towers have windows similar to those at the choir level. The windows of the bell gable are arched; the gables have domes decorated with tiles and topped by pinnacles.<ref name=\"hpip\"/><ref name=\"pa\"/>\n\n===Interior===\n\nThe interior has a rectangular plan with a single [[nave]], chancel, and two sacristies. A chapel dedicated to the Blessed Sacrament is located left of the altar. It has a separate door of glass and wood. The altar is simple with an altarpiece with a painting of the Holy Family. This painting, along with those of the walls of the chancel, are attributed to [[Jos\u00e9 Te\u00f3filo de Jesus]].<ref name=\"hpip\"/><ref name=\"pa\"/>\n\n==Protected status==\n\nThe Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus was listed as a historic structure by the [[National Institute of Historic and Artistic Heritage]] in 1941. It was listed in the Book of Historical Works as no. 294, and was a federally protected site in Laranjeiras.<ref name=\"iphan\"/>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"f\">{{cite book |last=Freire |first1=Felisbello |title=Hist\u00f3ria de Sergipe, (1575-1855) |location=Rio de Janeiro, Brasil |publisher=Typographia Perseverauza |year=1891 |page=207 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hpip\">{{cite web | last = Moura Filha | first = Maria Berthilde |url= https://hpip.org/en/Heritage/Details/1041 |title= Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus |place= Lisbon, Portugal |year = 2013|publisher=Heritage of Portuguese Influence/Patrim\u00f3nio de Influ\u00eancia Portuguesa |accessdate=2017-09-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"iphan\">{{cite web |url=http://portal.iphan.gov.br/uploads/ckfinder/arquivos/Lista%20de%20Processos%20de%20Tombamento.pdf |title=Lista de Processos de Tombamento |language=pt |place = Bras\u00edlia, Brazil |publisher=Instituto do Patrim\u00f4nio Hist\u00f3rico e Art\u00edstico Nacional |date=2020 |accessdate=2020-02-19 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"pa\">{{cite book |last=Passos |first1=Lucas Santos |title=Tombamentos de templos religiosos em Laranjeiras/Sergipe |location=S\u00e3o Crist\u00f3v\u00e3o |publisher=Universidade Federal de Sergipe |year=2015 |pages=35-39 |accessdate=2020-02-19 |url=https://ri.ufs.br/bitstream/riufs/6282/1/LUCAS_SANTOS_PASSOS.pdf |language = pt}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{commons category|Igreja Matriz do Sagrado Cora\u00e7\u00e3o de Jesus}}\n\n[[Category:Baroque church buildings in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic churches in Bahia]]\n[[Category:17th-century Roman Catholic church buildings]]\n[[Category:National heritage sites of Bahia]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Colonial architecture in Brazil]]\n[[Category:1709 establishments in the Portuguese Empire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox religious building\n| name = Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus\n| native_name = Igreja Matriz do Sagrado Cora\u00e7\u00e3o de Jesus\n| native_name_lang = pt\n| image = Igreja Matriz de Laranjeiras.jpg\n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus\n| map_type = Brazil\n| map_size = \n| map_alt = \n| map_relief = \n| map_caption = Location of the Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus in Brazil\n| coordinates = {{coord|-10.80509|-37.16631}}\n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| religious_affiliation=[[Catholic]]\n| rite=[[Roman Rite|Roman]]\n| sect = \n| tradition = \n| festival = <!-- or | festivals = -->\n| cercle = \n| sector = \n| municipality = [[Laranjeiras, Sergipe|Laranjeiras]]\n| district = \n| territory = \n| prefecture = \n| state = [[Sergipe]]\n| province = \n| region = \n| country = [[Brazil]]\n| administration = \n| consecration_year = \n| organisational_status = <!-- or | organizational_status = -->\n| functional_status = \n| heritage_designation = 1941\n| ownership = \n| governing_body = \n| leadership = \n| bhattaraka = \n| patron = \n| website = \n| architect = \n| architecture_type = \n| architecture_style = [[Baroque architecture|Baroque]]\n| founded_by = \n| creator = \n| funded_by = \n| general_contractor = \n| established = \n| groundbreaking = \n| year_completed = 1790s\n| construction_cost = \n| date_demolished = <!-- or | date_destroyed = -->\n| facade_direction = \n| capacity = \n| length = \n| width = \n| width_nave = \n| interior_area = \n| height_max = \n| dome_quantity = \n| dome_height_outer = \n| dome_height_inner = \n| dome_dia_outer = \n| dome_dia_inner = \n| spire_quantity = \n| spire_height = \n| site_area = \n| temple_quantity = \n| monument_quantity = \n| shrine_quantity = \n| inscriptions = \n| materials = \n| elevation_m =\n| elevation_footnotes = \n| nrhp = \n| designated = \n| added = \n| refnum = \n| footnotes = {{designation list|embed = yes| designation1 = Brazil| designation1_date = 1941|designation1_number =294}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus''' ({{lang-pt|Igreja Matriz do Sagrado Cora\u00e7\u00e3o de Jesus}}) is an 18-century [[Roman Catholic]] church in [[Laranjeiras, Sergipe|Laranjeiras]], [[Sergipe]], [[Brazil]]. It was the second church built in Laranjeiras, following the [[Church of Our Lady of the Conception of Comandaroba]], which was built by the Jesuits in the early 18th century. The church was listed as a historic structure by [[National Institute of Historic and Artistic Heritage]] (IPHAN) in 1941. The church is dedicated to the [[Sacred Heart|Sacred Heart of Jesus]] and is constructed in the [[Baroque architecture|Baroque style]]. The Parish Church belongs to the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Aracaju]].<ref name=\"hpip\"/><ref name=\"iphan\"/><ref name=\"pa\"/>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Outras agendas em Sergipe (27719738197).jpg|thumb|left|250px|View of fa\u00e7ade]]\n\nConstruction of Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus began at the end of the 18th century. Resident of Laranjeiras, then a district of [[Nossa Senhora do Socorro]] with a small port on the river, petitioned [[Maria I of Portugal|Queen Maria]] for the construction of a church in 1790. With the completion of the church, Laranjeiras had two churches: the Parish Church and the [[Church of Our Lady of the Conception of Comandaroba|Church of Our Lady of the Conception]], which belonged to the Comandaroba Plantation. The church was unable to accommodate the population of Laranjeiras, which grew rapidly in the 18th century, and the building was enlarged in 1905.<ref name=\"f\"/><ref name=\"hpip\"/>\n\n==Location==\n\nThe Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus is located on a high point above a bend in the [[Cotinguiba River]]. The church faces the river, but unusually, does not open to Pra\u00e7a da Matriz. The south fa\u00e7ade of the church, which faces the public square, has numerous small portals and windows.<ref name=\"hpip\"/>\n\n==Structure==\n\nThe building has a structure consisting of mixed masonry of stone and brick. The church has two bell towers with a monumental pediment at center. The pediment has volutes and is topped by a cross. There are three windows at the choir level and a low arch with glazed leaves and flags. The bell towers have windows similar to those at the choir level. The windows of the bell gable are arched; the gables have domes decorated with tiles and topped by pinnacles.<ref name=\"hpip\"/><ref name=\"pa\"/>\n\n===Interior===\n\nThe interior has a rectangular plan with a single [[nave]], chancel, and two sacristies. A chapel dedicated to the Blessed Sacrement is located left of the altar. It has a separate door of glass and wood. The altar is simple with an altarpiece with a painting of the Holy Family. This painting, along with those of the walls of the chancel, are attributed to [[Jos\u00e9 Te\u00f3filo de Jesus]].<ref name=\"hpip\"/><ref name=\"pa\"/>\n\n==Protected status==\n\nThe Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus was listed as a historic structure by the [[National Institute of Historic and Artistic Heritage]] in 1941. It was listed in the Book of Historical Works as no. 294, and was the federally protected site in Laranjeiras.<ref name=\"iphan\"/>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"f\">{{cite book |last=Freire |first1=Felisbello |title=Hist\u00f3ria de Sergipe, (1575-1855) |location=Rio de Janeiro, Brasil |publisher=Typographia Perseverauza |year=1891 |page=207 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hpip\">{{cite web | last = Moura Filha | first = Maria Berthilde |url= https://hpip.org/en/Heritage/Details/1041 |title= Parish Church of the Sacred Heart of Jesus |place= Lisbon, Portugal |year = 2013|publisher=Heritage of Portuguese Influence/Patrim\u00f3nio de Influ\u00eancia Portuguesa |accessdate=2017-09-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"iphan\">{{cite web |url=http://portal.iphan.gov.br/uploads/ckfinder/arquivos/Lista%20de%20Processos%20de%20Tombamento.pdf |title=Lista de Processos de Tombamento |language=pt |place = Bras\u00edlia, Brazil |publisher=Instituto do Patrim\u00f4nio Hist\u00f3rico e Art\u00edstico Nacional |date=2020 |accessdate=2020-02-19 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"pa\">{{cite book |last=Passos |first1=Lucas Santos |title=Tombamentos de templos religiosos em Laranjeiras/Sergipe |location=S\u00e3o Crist\u00f3v\u00e3o |publisher=Universidade Federal de Sergipe |year=2015 |pages=35-39 |accessdate=2020-02-19 |url=https://ri.ufs.br/bitstream/riufs/6282/1/LUCAS_SANTOS_PASSOS.pdf |language = pt}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{commons category|Igreja Matriz do Sagrado Cora\u00e7\u00e3o de Jesus}}\n\n[[Category:Baroque church buildings in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic churches in Bahia]]\n[[Category:17th-century Roman Catholic church buildings]]\n[[Category:National heritage sites of Bahia]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Colonial architecture in Brazil]]\n[[