{"title_page": "Rudy A. Cesena", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Notability|date=March 2020}}\n{{BLP unsourced|date=March 2020}}\n{{Underlinked|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Rudy A Cesena\n|occupation=Physicist\n|birth_date=1933 \n}}\n\nRudy A Cesena, was a physicist on [[Project Orion (nuclear propulsion)|Project Orion]].\n\nHe was born in 1933. Graduated from Hoover Senior High Class of 1951. He went to [[San Diego State University]] Class of 1961. \n \n==Career==\nWorked at Naval Electronics Lab, 1951 to 1959. General Atomic, 1959 to 1972. He later worked on a paper \"Effects of space radiation on lasers\" with D.M.J Compton.\n\n==Project Orion==\nRudy would work in the gypsum mines and then meet the experimental physicists working on the model tests for Project Orion. He would go down to the testing area for Project Orion.\n\nRudy's name appears on \"GAMD-1212\" - 26 January 1960, \"Development of a meter-diameter explosion-propelled flying model\". \"The Nuclear/Chemical Pulse Reaction Propulsion Project\". Cesena is also on the distribution list for the Safety Procedures at Point Loma Experimental Site (Dunne, Brian B., GAMD-915, 17 July 1959)\n\n==Later career==\nIRT Corporation, 1972 to 1989. Then later returned to General Atomics, 1989 to 1990.\n\n* https://ntrs.nasa.gov/search.jsp?R=19660030621\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cesena, Rudy}}\n[[Category:1933 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American physicists]]\n[[Category:San Diego State University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Notability|date=March 2020}}\n{{BLP unsourced|date=March 2020}}\n{{Underlinked|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Rudy A Cesena\n|occupation=Physicist\n|birth_date=1933 \n}}\n\nRudy A Cesena, was a physicist on [[Project Orion (nuclear propulsion)|Project Orion]].\n\nHe was born in 1933. Graduated from Hoover Senior High Class of 1951. He went to San Diego State University Class of 1961. \n \n==Career==\nWorked at Naval Electronics Lab, 1951 to 1959. General Atomic, 1959 to 1972. He later worked on a paper \"Effects of space radiation on lasers\" with D.M.J Compton.\n\n==Project Orion==\nRudy would work in the gypsum mines and then meet the experimental physicists working on the model tests for Project Orion. He would go down to the testing area for Project Orion.\n\nRudy's name appears on \"GAMD-1212\" - 26 January 1960, \"Development of a meter-diameter explosion-propelled flying model\". \"The Nuclear/Chemical Pulse Reaction Propulsion Project\". Cesena is also on the distribution list for the Safety Procedures at Point Loma Experimental Site (Dunne, Brian B., GAMD-915, 17 July 1959)\n\n==Later career==\nIRT Corporation, 1972 to 1989. Then later returned to General Atomics, 1989 to 1990.\n\n* https://ntrs.nasa.gov/search.jsp?R=19660030621\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cesena, Rudy}}\n[[Category:1933 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American physicists]]\n[[Category:San Diego State University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Pikaryaa", "label": "safe", "comment": "added link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rudy_A._Cesena"}
{"title_page": "Seven minutes in heaven", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=January 2020}}\n{{Other uses}}\n'''Seven minutes in heaven''' (also known as '''two''', '''five''', '''seven''', or '''ten minutes in the closet''', etc.) is a [[kissing game|kissing]] [[party game]] played at teenage parties.\n\n==The game==\nTwo people are selected to go into a closet or other dark enclosed space and do whatever they like for seven minutes. It is common for the participants to [[kiss]] or [[Making out|make out]], but they may instead choose to talk, engage in some other (usually quiet) activity, or simply do nothing at all and wait for the time to expire. \n\nThe participants can be selected by various methods, such as [[Spin the bottle|spinning a bottle]], drawing lots or votes.\n\n==History ==\nThe game has been recorded as early as 1953.<ref name=jet>{{cite magazine |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mkIDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA22 |title=New Game Called '7 Minutes in Heaven' |magazine=[[Jet (magazine)|Jet]] |date=6 August 1953 |page=22}}</ref>\n\n== In popular culture (ordered by year) ==\n* In the 1985 movie ''[[Teen Wolf]]'', Scott Howard and Lisa \"Boof\" Marconi are selected to go in a closet in a version of '''Seven minutes in heaven'''.\n* ''[[Seven Minutes in Heaven (film)|Seven Minutes in Heaven]]'' is a 1985 teen film directed by Linda Feferman and starring [[Jennifer Connelly]] in one of her first film roles.\n* November 18, 1994, in ''[[Boy Meets World]]'' Season 2, Episode 9 (\u201cFear Strikes Out\u201d), Cory is worried about who will be joining him in the closet to [[Making out|make out]]. Luckily it turns out to be his friend Topanga, who informs Cory that they do not have to do anything. They spend most of the time discussing what they should do. Seconds before they agree to kiss, the door opens. \n* November 3, 2002, in ''[[King of the Hill]]'' Season 7, Episode 1 (\"Get Your Freak Off\"), Bobby Hill is forced to play '''the game''' with a girl from his school. Bobby and the girl sit in the closet and talk (getting to know each other in the process), followed by the girl starting to unbutton his shirt, until Hank Hill (Bobby's father) pulls open the door and stops them.\n* In the 2004 movie ''[[13 Going on 30]]'', \"13\"-year-old Jenna Rink waits in a closet to play the game, but her supposed friends prank her with the wrong boy. Upset, she makes the wish to be 30.\n* April 26, 2004, in ''[[The Bernie Mac Show]]'' Season 3, Episode 19 (\"The Talk\"), Jordan and his friends play '''the game''' at a party. Jordan kisses a girl and later believes that he has impregnated her.  \n* The 2005 album ''[[From Under The Cork Tree]]'' of the American band [[Fall Out Boy]] has a song on it called \"7 Minutes in Heaven (Atavan Halen)\".\n* At the beginning of the 2007 film ''[[Good Luck Chuck]]'', the titular character rejects a [[Goth subculture|Goth]] girl when playing '''the game'''. Humiliated, she puts a curse on him, kicking off the plot.\n* Between September 30 and December 02, 2008, in ''[[Paris Hilton's My New BFF]]'' Season 1, Episode 5 (\"You Gotta Have Class\"), the contestants play '''Seven minutes in heaven''' with rapper [[Dirt Nasty]] in a closet as a challenge to test their discretion.\n* [[Seven Minutes in Heaven (play)|Seven Minutes in Heaven]], a play by Steven Levenson, first produced in 2009 in a workshop at Ars Nova. \n* [[Mike_O%27Brien_(actor)#7_Minutes_in_Heaven_with_Mike_O'Brien|7 Minutes in Heaven with Mike O'Brien]], a web series created in 2011.\n* ''Seven Hours in Heaven'' is a 2015 film written and directed by Kyle Gerkin where three couples play an adult variation of the game.\n* 2015/2016, in ''[[Modern Family]]'' Season 7, Luke and Manny host a party for some exchange students whom they want to impress. The girls ask \"When are we going to play '''Seven minutes in heaven'''?\"\n* March 18, 2016, [[Seven Minutes in Heaven (Daredevil)|\"Seven Minutes in Heaven\"]], episode 9 of ''Daredevil''.\n* 2016 the song [[Slumber Party (song)|''Slumber Party'']] (general information on [[slumber party]]) of the American singer [[Britney Spears]] refers to the game '''Seven Minutes in Heaven'''.\n* February 16, 2018, in ''[[Everything Sucks!]]'' Season 1, Episode 4 (\"Romeo & Juliet in Space\"), the four main characters (McQuaid, Tyler, Luke, and Kate) indulge in '''the game''' with the members of the drama club.\n\n==References== \n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Party games}}\n\n[[Category:Kissing games]]\n[[Category:Party games]]\n\n\n{{Game-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=January 2020}}\n{{Other uses}}\n'''Seven minutes in heaven''' (also known as '''two''', '''five''', '''seven''', or '''ten minutes in the closet''', etc.) is a [[kissing game|kissing]] [[party game]] played at teenage parties.\n\n==The game==\nTwo people are selected to go into a closet or other dark enclosed space and do whatever they like for seven minutes. It is common for the participants to [[kiss]] or [[Making out|make out]], but they may instead choose to talk, engage in some other (usually quiet) activity, or simply do nothing at all and wait for the time to expire. \n\nThe participants can be selected by various methods, such as [[Spin the bottle|spinning a bottle]], drawing lots or votes.\n\n==History ==\nThe game has been recorded as early as 1953.<ref name=jet>{{cite magazine |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mkIDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA22 |title=New Game Called '7 Minutes in Heaven' |magazine=[[Jet (magazine)|Jet]] |date=6 August 1953 |page=22}}</ref>\n\n== In popular culture (ordered by year) ==\n* In the 1985 movie ''[[Teen Wolf]]'', Scott Howard and Lisa \"Boof\" Marconi are selected to go in a closet in a version of '''Seven minutes in heaven'''.\n* ''[[Seven Minutes in Heaven (film)|Seven Minutes in Heaven]]'' is a 1985 teen film directed by Linda Feferman and starring [[Jennifer Connelly]] in one of her first film roles.\n* November 18, 1994, in ''[[Boy Meets World]]'' Season 2, Episode 9 (\u201cFear Strikes Out\u201d), Cory is worried about who will be joining him in the closet to [[Making out|make out]]. Luckily it turns out to be his friend Topanga, who informs Cory that they do not have to do anything. They spend most of the time discussing what they should do. Seconds before they agree to kiss, the door opens. \n* November 3, 2002, in ''[[King of the Hill]]'' Season 7, Episode 1 (\"Get Your Freak Off\"), Bobby Hill is forced to play the game with a girl from his school. Bobby and the girl sit in the closet and talk (getting to know each other in the process), followed by the girl starting to unbutton his shirt, until Hank Hill (Bobby's father) pulls open the door and stops them.\n* In the 2004 movie ''[[13 Going on 30]]'', \"13\"-year-old Jenna Rink waits in a closet to play the game, but her supposed friends prank her with the wrong boy. Upset, she makes the wish to be 30.\n* April 26, 2004, in ''[[The Bernie Mac Show]]'' Season 3, Episode 19 (\"The Talk\"), Jordan and his friends play '''the game''' at a party. Jordan kisses a girl and later believes that he has impregnated her.  \n* The 2005 album ''[[From Under The Cork Tree]]'' of the American band [[Fall Out Boy]] has a song on it called \"7 Minutes in Heaven (Atavan Halen)\".\n* At the beginning of the 2007 film ''[[Good Luck Chuck]]'', the titular character rejects a [[Goth subculture|Goth]] girl when playing '''the game'''. Humiliated, she puts a curse on him, kicking off the plot.\n* Between September 30 and December 02, 2008, in ''[[Paris Hilton's My New BFF]]'' Season 1, Episode 5 (\"You Gotta Have Class\"), the contestants play '''Seven minutes in heaven''' with rapper [[Dirt Nasty]] in a closet as a challenge to test their discretion.\n* [[Seven Minutes in Heaven (play)|Seven Minutes in Heaven]], a play by Steven Levenson, first produced in 2009 in a workshop at Ars Nova. \n* [[Mike_O%27Brien_(actor)#7_Minutes_in_Heaven_with_Mike_O'Brien|7 Minutes in Heaven with Mike O'Brien]], a web series created in 2011.\n* ''Seven Hours in Heaven'' is a 2015 film written and directed by Kyle Gerkin where three couples play an adult variation of the game.\n* 2015/2016, in ''[[Modern Family]]'' Season 7, Luke and Manny host a party for some exchange students whom they want to impress. The girls ask \"When are we going to play '''Seven minutes in heaven'''?\"\n* March 18, 2016, [[Seven Minutes in Heaven (Daredevil)|\"Seven Minutes in Heaven\"]], episode 9 of ''Daredevil''.\n* 2016 the song [[Slumber Party (song)|''Slumber Party'']] (general information on [[slumber party]]) of the American singer [[Britney Spears]] refers to the game '''Seven Minutes in Heaven'''.\n* February 16, 2018, in ''[[Everything Sucks!]]'' Season 1, Episode 4 (\"Romeo & Juliet in Space\"), the four main characters (McQuaid, Tyler, Luke, and Kate) indulge in '''the game''' with the members of the drama club.\n\n==References== \n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Party games}}\n\n[[Category:Kissing games]]\n[[Category:Party games]]\n\n\n{{Game-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Steue", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eIn popular culture (ordered by year):Fattened \"the game\" because it stands for the term of this article.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seven_minutes_in_heaven"}
{"title_page": "Ashok Amritraj", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Ashok Amritraj\n| image       = AA-Headshot BlackSuit.jpg\n| country     =  \n| residence   =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1956|2|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| citizenship = [[Americans|American]]\n}}\n\n'''Ashok Amritraj''' (born 22 February 1956)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1090221/jsp/entertainment/story_10566759.jsp|title=Slumdog will sweep | location=Calcutta, India | work=The Telegraph|first=Amit|last=Roy|date=21 February 2009}}</ref> is Chairman and CEO of the Hyde Park Entertainment Group, and was formerly CEO of National Geographic Films.\n\nAn internationally renowned award-winning producer, Amritraj has made over 100 films during the span of his 35-year career, with worldwide revenues in excess of $2 billion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/bc1dde3e-1f36-11e9-a46f-08f9738d6b2b|title=Subscribe to read|website=Financial Times|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> He has partnered with every major studio in Hollywood and produced films starring the likes of Dwayne \"The Rock\" Johnson,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/film/markets-festivals/the-rock-is-walking-tall-1117879320/|title=The Rock is \u2018Walking Tall\u2019|last=Fleming|first=Michael|last2=Fleming|first2=Michael|date=2003-01-23|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Robert De Niro,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://businessworld.in/article/It-Is-The-Time-Of-Disruption-Ashok-Amritraj-/24-08-2018-158465|title=It Is The Time Of Disruption: Ashok Amritraj|last=Jha|first=Manish Kumar|website=BW Businessworld|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Bruce Willis, Sandra Bullock, Sylvester Stallone, Angelina Jolie, Cate Blanchett, Dustin Hoffman, Andrew Garfield, Steve Martin, Antonio Banderas,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://businessworld.in/article/It-Is-The-Time-Of-Disruption-Ashok-Amritraj-/24-08-2018-158465|title=It Is The Time Of Disruption: Ashok Amritraj|last=Jha|first=Manish Kumar|website=BW Businessworld|language=en|access-date=2019-07-30}}</ref> Jennifer Aniston,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2013/09/toronto-lionsgateroadside-near-u-s-deal-for-elmore-leonards-life-of-crime-584138/|title=Toronto: Elmore Leonard\u2019s \u2018Life Of Crime\u2019 Near U.S. Deal With Lionsgate/Roadside|last=Jr|first=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|date=2013-09-11|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Nicolas Cage,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ghostrider2-idUSTRE81F19720120216|title=\"Ghost Rider 2\" poised to ignite lackluster franchise|date=2012-02-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-07-03|language=en}}</ref> and many more.\n\nAmritraj\u2019s extraordinary career from Wimbledon tennis player to billion dollar Hollywood producer (chronicled in his autobiography Advantage Hollywood<ref>{{Cite book|title=Advantage Hollywood|last=Amritraj|first=Ashok|publisher=Harper Collins Publishers India|year=2013|isbn=978-93-5029-359-1|location=India|pages=}}</ref>) is matched only by his commitment to education, diversity, and gender equality. Dedicating a significant amount of his time to philanthropic endeavors worldwide, in 2016 Amritraj was appointed as the first United Nations India Goodwill Ambassador for the 17 UN Sustainable Development Goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/biz/news/hyde-park-ashok-amritraj-un-india-1201974655/|title=Hyde Park Entertainment\u2019s Ashok Amritraj on His New Role as India Goodwill Ambassador|last=Frater|first=Patrick|last2=Frater|first2=Patrick|date=2017-02-02|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> In December 2018, by decree of the President of the Republic of France, Amritraj was appointed a Chevalier (Knight) of the Ordre National du Merit\u00e9.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/ashok-amritraj-decorated-french-government-1203089843/|title=Ashok Amritraj Decorated by French Government|last=Frater|first=Patrick|last2=Frater|first2=Patrick|date=2018-12-14|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\nAmritraj has grown Hyde Park into a cutting-edge independent alternative to the traditional Hollywood system, fully realizing his vision for a progressive global company that incorporates the most essential elements of a full-fledged studio. Hyde Park\u2019s mandate encompasses feature film, television, digital, documentary, and local language content, with the Company possessing development, production, and financing capabilities in addition to handling worldwide sales and marketing.\n\nAmritraj has had box office hits such as [[Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance]], starring Nicolas Cage,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-xpm-2012-feb-17-la-fi-ct-projector-20120217-story.html|title=Movie Projector: 'Ghost Rider' sequel to scorch competition|date=2012-02-17|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2019-07-03|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref> [[Bringing Down the House (film)|Bringing Down the House]], starring Steve Martin,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/film/reviews/bringing-down-the-house-1200543214/|title=Bringing Down the House|last=McCarthy|first=Todd|last2=McCarthy|first2=Todd|date=2003-02-23|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> [[Premonition (2007 film)|Premonition]], starring Sandra Bullock,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/mcmahon-premonition-tristar-31081/|title=McMahon Has 'Premonition' for TriStar|date=2005-11-10|website=www.backstage.com|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> [[Walking Tall (2004 film)|Walking Tall]] starring The Rock, and many more, as well as critically acclaimed titles including [[99 Homes]] starring Andrew Garfield and Michael Shannon, [[Blue Valentine (film)|Blue Valentine]] starring Ryan Gosling and Michelle Williams,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hydeparkentertainment.com/news/2019/6/5/blue-valentine-is-an-indie-film|title=Right Cinema: Blue Valentine is an Indie Film|website=Hyde Park Entertainment Group|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and [[Shopgirl]], starring Steve Martin and Claire Danes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/scene/markets-festivals/fox-takes-international-on-hyde-park-shopgirl-1117892612/|title=Fox takes international on Hyde Park \u2018Shopgirl\u2019|last=Brodesser|first=Cathy Dunkley,Claude|last2=Dunkley|first2=Cathy|date=2003-09-18|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03|last3=Brodesser|first3=Claude}}</ref>\n\nAmritraj\u2019s current projects include: supernatural thriller, [[Prey (2019 American film)|Prey]], in partnership with Blumhouse Productions,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/06/prey-logan-miller-blumhouse-hyde-park-1201769872/|title=Hyde Park-Image Nation & Blumhouse Partner For \u2018Prey\u2019|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|last2=D'Alessandro|first2=Anthony|date=2016-06-09|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Pashmina, a Major Animated Musical in partnership with Netflix, to be directed by Gurinder Chadha and with music by Oscar-winner A.R. Rahman,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/pashmina-gurinder-chadha-nidhi-chanani-netflix-ashok-amritraj-hyde-park-animated-musical-india-blinded-by-the-light-1202570675/|title=Netflix Teams With Gurinder Chadha & Ashok Amritraj\u2019s Hyde Park To Turn Nidhi Chanani Graphic Novel \u2018Pashmina\u2019 Into Animated Musical|last=Jr|first=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|date=2019-03-06|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and Fordlandia, a Television event series, to be directed by Werner Herzog at AMC Studios.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/fordlandia-novel-adapted-tv-werner-herzog-direct-greg-grandin-hyde-park-entertainment-group-1202410725/|title=\u2018Fordlandia\u2019 Novel Being Adapted For TV; Werner Herzog To Direct|last=Petski|first=Denise|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|date=2018-06-14|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\nHyde Park Entertainment Group and its artists have received awards and recognition from the major award shows and film festivals including the Oscars, the BAFTA awards, the Emmys, the Independent Spirit Awards, the Cannes Film Festival, the Golden Globes, and many more.\n\nAmritraj serves on the Producers Executive Board of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiawest.com/online_features/ashok-amritraj---hollywood-film-producer/article_f071eed0-db90-11e3-b969-0019bb2963f4.html|title=ASHOK AMRITRAJ - Hollywood Film Producer|website=India West|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and on the advisory board for the Dodge Film School at Chapman University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.chapman.edu/dodge/2017/08/16/dodge-college-moves-up-to-6-spot-in-the-hollywood-reporters-annual-ranking-of-top-25-film-schools/|title=Dodge College Moves Up to #6 Spot in The Hollywood Reporter\u2019s Annual Ranking of Top 25 Film Schools - Maintains \u2018Top 10\u2019 Status for 5th Consecutive Year|website=Dodge College of Film and Media Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> In 2015, he was bestowed an honorary Doctorate of the Arts from the University of East London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/sports/ashok-amritraj-awarded-honorary-doctorate-by-a-london-varsity/articleshow/49842998.cms|title=Ashok Amritraj awarded honorary doctorate by a London Varsity|date=2015-11-19|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAshok lived in Chennai his mother's name is Maggie Dhairyam and father's name is Robert Amritraj. He has two brothers, [[Vijay Amritraj]] and Anand Amritraj, both international tennis players.\n\n==Personal life==\n\n==Filmography==\n===As Producer===\n* ''[[Prey (2019 American film)|Prey]]'' (2019)\n* ''[[Killing Hasselhoff]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Careful What You Wish For (film)|Careful What You Wish For]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[99 Homes]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Life of Crime (film)|Life of Crime]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[The Double (2011 film)|The Double]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[Dylan Dog: Dead of Night]]'' (2011)\n* ''Killer'' (2010)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/19233|title=Hyde Park Hunts Latest 'Killer'}}</ref>\n* ''Risen: The Story of the First Easter'' (2009) \n* ''[[Dark Country]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[Street Fighter: The Legend of Chun-Li]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[The Other End of the Line]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Asylum (2008 film)|Asylum]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Death Sentence (2007 film)|Death Sentence]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Premonition (2007 film)|Premonition]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Raising Helen]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Walking Tall (2004 film)|Walking Tall]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Bringing Down the House (film)|Bringing Down the House]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[What's the Worst That Could Happen?]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Bandits_(2001_film)|Bandits]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[If... Dog... Rabbit...]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[The White Raven (1998 film)|The White Raven]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[A Murder of Crows (film)|A Murder of Crows]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Billy Frankenstein]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Black Thunder (film)|Black Thunder]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Jeans (1998 film)|Jeans]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Strategic Command (film)|Strategic Command]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[The Shooter (1997 film)|The Shooter]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Inferno (1997 film)|Inferno]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Steel Sharks (film) | Steel Sharks]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Night Hunter (1996 film)|Night Hunter]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[Illicit Dreams]]'' (1994)\n* ''[[Night Eyes 3]]'' (1993)\n* ''Snapdragon'' (1993)\n* ''Tropical Heat'' (1993)\n* ''Sexual Response'' (1992)\n* ''Illicit Behavior'' (1992)\n*'' Night Eyes 2'' (1992)\n* ''[[Double Impact]]'' (1991)\n* ''Eyewitness to Murder'' (1991)\n* ''[[Popcorn (1991 film)|Popcorn]]'' (1991)\n* ''[[Night Eyes]]'' (1990)\n* ''[[Bloodstone (1988 film)|Bloodstone]]'' (1988) (co-producer)\n* ''[[School Spirit]]'' (1985)\n* ''Nine Deaths of the Ninja'' (1985)\n\n===As Executive Producer===\n* ''[[Machete (2010 film)|Machete]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Traitor (film)|Traitor]]'' (2008)\n* ''Dead of Night'' (2009)\n* ''[[Battle in Seattle]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Trade (film)|Trade]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Dreamer (2005 film)|Dreamer]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Moonlight Mile (film)|Moonlight Mile]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[Original Sin (2001 film)|Original Sin]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Antitrust (film)|Antitrust]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Get Carter (2000 film)|Get Carter]]'' (2000)\n* ''[[Battlefield Earth (film)|Battlefield Earth]]'' (2000)\n* ''The White River Kid'' (1999)\n* ''[[The Boondock Saints]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[Five Aces]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[The Confession (1999 film)|The Confession]]'' (1999)\n* ''Scorned 2'' (1997)\n* ''Electra'' (1996)\n* ''Victim of Desire'' (1995)\n* ''Red Sun Rising'' (1994)\n* ''Scorned'' (1994)\n* ''The Killing Machine'' (1994)\n* ''[[Last Call (1991 film)|Last Call]]'' (1991)\n* ''The Jigsaw Murders'' (1988)\n* ''Smart Alec'' (1986)\n* ''Fleshburn'' (1984)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{ATP}}\n* {{ITF}}\n* {{IMDb name|2170}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amritraj, Ashok}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American film producers of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:Indian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Film producers from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Indian male tennis players]]\n[[Category:American businessmen of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:Amritraj family]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Ashok Amritraj\n| image       = AA-Headshot BlackSuit.jpg\n| country     =  \n| residence   =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1956|2|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| citizenship = [[Americans|American]]\n}}\n\n'''Ashok Amritraj''' (born 22 February 1956)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1090221/jsp/entertainment/story_10566759.jsp|title=Slumdog will sweep | location=Calcutta, India | work=The Telegraph|first=Amit|last=Roy|date=21 February 2009}}</ref> is Chairman and CEO of the Hyde Park Entertainment Group, and was formerly CEO of National Geographic Films.\n\nAn internationally renowned award-winning producer, Amritraj has made over 100 films during the span of his 35-year career, with worldwide revenues in excess of $2 billion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/bc1dde3e-1f36-11e9-a46f-08f9738d6b2b|title=Subscribe to read|website=Financial Times|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> He has partnered with every major studio in Hollywood and produced films starring the likes of Dwayne \"The Rock\" Johnson,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/film/markets-festivals/the-rock-is-walking-tall-1117879320/|title=The Rock is \u2018Walking Tall\u2019|last=Fleming|first=Michael|last2=Fleming|first2=Michael|date=2003-01-23|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Robert De Niro,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://businessworld.in/article/It-Is-The-Time-Of-Disruption-Ashok-Amritraj-/24-08-2018-158465|title=It Is The Time Of Disruption: Ashok Amritraj|last=Jha|first=Manish Kumar|website=BW Businessworld|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Bruce Willis, Sandra Bullock, Sylvester Stallone, Angelina Jolie, Cate Blanchett, Dustin Hoffman, Andrew Garfield, Steve Martin, Antonio Banderas,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://businessworld.in/article/It-Is-The-Time-Of-Disruption-Ashok-Amritraj-/24-08-2018-158465|title=It Is The Time Of Disruption: Ashok Amritraj|last=Jha|first=Manish Kumar|website=BW Businessworld|language=en|access-date=2019-07-30}}</ref> Jennifer Aniston,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2013/09/toronto-lionsgateroadside-near-u-s-deal-for-elmore-leonards-life-of-crime-584138/|title=Toronto: Elmore Leonard\u2019s \u2018Life Of Crime\u2019 Near U.S. Deal With Lionsgate/Roadside|last=Jr|first=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|date=2013-09-11|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Nicolas Cage,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ghostrider2-idUSTRE81F19720120216|title=\"Ghost Rider 2\" poised to ignite lackluster franchise|date=2012-02-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-07-03|language=en}}</ref> and many more.\n\nAmritraj\u2019s extraordinary career from Wimbledon tennis player to billion dollar Hollywood producer (chronicled in his autobiography Advantage Hollywood<ref>{{Cite book|title=Advantage Hollywood|last=Amritraj|first=Ashok|publisher=Harper Collins Publishers India|year=2013|isbn=978-93-5029-359-1|location=India|pages=}}</ref>) is matched only by his commitment to education, diversity, and gender equality. Dedicating a significant amount of his time to philanthropic endeavors worldwide, in 2016 Amritraj was appointed as the first United Nations India Goodwill Ambassador for the 17 UN Sustainable Development Goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/biz/news/hyde-park-ashok-amritraj-un-india-1201974655/|title=Hyde Park Entertainment\u2019s Ashok Amritraj on His New Role as India Goodwill Ambassador|last=Frater|first=Patrick|last2=Frater|first2=Patrick|date=2017-02-02|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> In December 2018, by decree of the President of the Republic of France, Amritraj was appointed a Chevalier (Knight) of the Ordre National du Merit\u00e9.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/ashok-amritraj-decorated-french-government-1203089843/|title=Ashok Amritraj Decorated by French Government|last=Frater|first=Patrick|last2=Frater|first2=Patrick|date=2018-12-14|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\nAmritraj has grown Hyde Park into a cutting-edge independent alternative to the traditional Hollywood system, fully realizing his vision for a progressive global company that incorporates the most essential elements of a full-fledged studio. Hyde Park\u2019s mandate encompasses feature film, television, digital, documentary, and local language content, with the Company possessing development, production, and financing capabilities in addition to handling worldwide sales and marketing.\n\nAmritraj has had box office hits such as [[Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance]], starring Nicolas Cage,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-xpm-2012-feb-17-la-fi-ct-projector-20120217-story.html|title=Movie Projector: 'Ghost Rider' sequel to scorch competition|date=2012-02-17|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2019-07-03|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref> [[Bringing Down the House (film)|Bringing Down the House]], starring Steve Martin,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/film/reviews/bringing-down-the-house-1200543214/|title=Bringing Down the House|last=McCarthy|first=Todd|last2=McCarthy|first2=Todd|date=2003-02-23|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> [[Premonition (2007 film)|Premonition]], starring Sandra Bullock,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/mcmahon-premonition-tristar-31081/|title=McMahon Has 'Premonition' for TriStar|date=2005-11-10|website=www.backstage.com|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> [[Walking Tall (2004 film)|Walking Tall]] starring The Rock, and many more, as well as critically acclaimed titles including [[99 Homes]] starring Andrew Garfield and Michael Shannon, [[Blue Valentine (film)|Blue Valentine]] starring Ryan Gosling and Michelle Williams,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hydeparkentertainment.com/news/2019/6/5/blue-valentine-is-an-indie-film|title=Right Cinema: Blue Valentine is an Indie Film|website=Hyde Park Entertainment Group|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and [[Shopgirl]], starring Steve Martin and Claire Danes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/scene/markets-festivals/fox-takes-international-on-hyde-park-shopgirl-1117892612/|title=Fox takes international on Hyde Park \u2018Shopgirl\u2019|last=Brodesser|first=Cathy Dunkley,Claude|last2=Dunkley|first2=Cathy|date=2003-09-18|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03|last3=Brodesser|first3=Claude}}</ref>\n\nAmritraj\u2019s current projects include: supernatural thriller, [[Prey (2019 American film)|Prey]], in partnership with Blumhouse Productions,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/06/prey-logan-miller-blumhouse-hyde-park-1201769872/|title=Hyde Park-Image Nation & Blumhouse Partner For \u2018Prey\u2019|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|last2=D'Alessandro|first2=Anthony|date=2016-06-09|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Pashmina, a Major Animated Musical in partnership with Netflix, to be directed by Gurinder Chadha and with music by Oscar-winner A.R. Rahman,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/pashmina-gurinder-chadha-nidhi-chanani-netflix-ashok-amritraj-hyde-park-animated-musical-india-blinded-by-the-light-1202570675/|title=Netflix Teams With Gurinder Chadha & Ashok Amritraj\u2019s Hyde Park To Turn Nidhi Chanani Graphic Novel \u2018Pashmina\u2019 Into Animated Musical|last=Jr|first=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|date=2019-03-06|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and FORDLANDIA, a Television event series, to be directed by Werner Herzog at AMC Studios.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/fordlandia-novel-adapted-tv-werner-herzog-direct-greg-grandin-hyde-park-entertainment-group-1202410725/|title=\u2018Fordlandia\u2019 Novel Being Adapted For TV; Werner Herzog To Direct|last=Petski|first=Denise|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|date=2018-06-14|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\nHyde Park Entertainment Group and its artists have received awards and recognition from the major award shows and film festivals including the Oscars, the BAFTA awards, the Emmys, the Independent Spirit Awards, the Cannes Film Festival, the Golden Globes, and many more.\n\nAmritraj serves on the Producers Executive Board of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiawest.com/online_features/ashok-amritraj---hollywood-film-producer/article_f071eed0-db90-11e3-b969-0019bb2963f4.html|title=ASHOK AMRITRAJ - Hollywood Film Producer|website=India West|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and on the advisory board for the Dodge Film School at Chapman University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.chapman.edu/dodge/2017/08/16/dodge-college-moves-up-to-6-spot-in-the-hollywood-reporters-annual-ranking-of-top-25-film-schools/|title=Dodge College Moves Up to #6 Spot in The Hollywood Reporter\u2019s Annual Ranking of Top 25 Film Schools - Maintains \u2018Top 10\u2019 Status for 5th Consecutive Year|website=Dodge College of Film and Media Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> In 2015, he was bestowed an honorary Doctorate of the Arts from the University of East London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/sports/ashok-amritraj-awarded-honorary-doctorate-by-a-london-varsity/articleshow/49842998.cms|title=Ashok Amritraj awarded honorary doctorate by a London Varsity|date=2015-11-19|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAshok lived in Chennai his mother's name is Maggie Dhairyam and father's name is Robert Amritraj. He has two brothers, [[Vijay Amritraj]] and Anand Amritraj, both international tennis players.\n\n==Personal life==\n\n==Filmography==\n===As Producer===\n* ''[[Prey (2019 American film)|Prey]]'' (2019)\n* ''[[Killing Hasselhoff]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Careful What You Wish For (film)|Careful What You Wish For]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[99 Homes]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Life of Crime (film)|Life of Crime]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[The Double (2011 film)|The Double]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[Dylan Dog: Dead of Night]]'' (2011)\n* ''Killer'' (2010)<ref>{{cite 